        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 8:30PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 830 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles north of Pickens, or near Table Rock State Park, moving north
at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Table Rock State Park, Caesars Head State Park, and Pumpkintown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
